# Development Workflow

## Getting Started
1. Install dependencies using `npm install`
2. Run development server with `npm run dev`
3. Build production version with `npm run build`
4. Start production server with `npm run start`

## Project Scripts
All scripts are defined in [package.json](mdc:package.json):
- `dev`: Runs development server
- `build`: Creates production build
- `start`: Starts production server
- `lint`: Runs ESLint

## Development Process
1. Create new components in [src/components](mdc:src/components)
2. Add new pages in [src/pages](mdc:src/pages)
3. Update styles in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)
4. Use Next.js features from [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs)

## Code Quality
- ESLint is configured for code quality
- Prettier handles code formatting
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Keep components and functions focused and well-documented
